FBIS4-5038 "dreas067_l_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 Philippines Ramos Announces Appointments for Military Commands Ramos Announces Appointments for Military Commands BK0704073394 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network in Tagalog 0930 GMT 6 Apr 94 BK0704073394 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network in Tagalog 0930 GMT 6 Apr 94 Tagalog BFN [Text] President Ramos has made additional appointments for the Armed Forces. Major General Orlando Soriano of the Philippine Army will lead the Southern Command. He will replace Lieutenant General Thelmo Cunanan, who is going to retire on 14 April. Brigadier Edgardo Batenga will be the new Northern Luzon Commander. He will replace Soriano. Batenga's replacement as 5th Infantry Division chief is Brigadier General Romeo (Padiernos). Nineteen officials, including General Lisandro Abadia, will officially retire this year.
